tasks.text: will match (depending on your settings almost) anything, but only a single character. ? will make the preceding element optional, i.e. appearing not at all or exactly once. * will match the preceding element multiple times, i.e. not at all or an unlimited amount of times. This will match as many characters as possible. If you combine both to *? you'll get a ungreedy match, essentially matching as few characters as possible (down to 0).
